thank you for the response.  We are looking to be full timers. Getting rid of all our things and get one to live out of. So trying to get s lot of input on them. Thanks again and enjoy!

we had to order our as a costume they said 4-6 weeks. I guess they do normally come out at that time but my husband change to the 2016. So the 4-6 weeks turned out to be 2 months and 2 weeks. So just incase have a plan B on who or where you can stay if they give you the option on upgrading to 2017. It's not going to be weeks it will be months and can be very very stressful. Also the 2016 was definitely worth the wait just wish they would have said it could take longer. Now they should be ok but still plan b I had to stay in tahoe for a month in a half and stayed with my parents the rest of the time. My in laws are not an option right now so it was hard to do. But we had to do it that way the rates in the bay area are outrageous for a motel 6! So the 2016 has a beautiful interior :) I like it feels like a home looks classy compared to the 2015 was not my favorite. Also 2016 they give you the option for a table with 4 chairs instead of the booth. Also another tip when you are getting the credit background checked for the trailer  never have an rv park show up before approval on you score history. Credit company might not let you get it if they see you will be living in it. Wait till the credit background is cleared. Then you can look for a park that is the trick we were told about and we did it that way and worked out fine. We waited a while and then moved to the rv park lol even the guy was like good you are smart not having an rv place on your history yet. This is my biggest tip to you the Jayco headquarters are in Indiana they transport one trialer at a time. Also the plant pushed the 2016 back and our model was at the end of assembly a nightmare for the worthy upgrade. I hope it helps and best of luck to you  guys :). We went Jayco because it was a good starter and had many different budget selections and depending on credit you can go really big lol.

we have the outdoor kitchen has a sink, a mini fridge, and a little burner. Which has been a blessing you are doing work outside you just open the slide wash your hands. No tracking it inside also mini fridge is normally the extra storage to over flow from inside. They give you patios on two bathrooms I think we have one and works fine for us. The fridge inside the place is a big one full sized just shallow but others have small fridges. So that was nice on the upgrade it's stainless steel :). We only go the one ac but if voltage is not an issue then two is nice takes time to cool my son's room with the one. But the kitchen living area and my room are cold! The ac is powerful and ud be wearing sweaters at times ha. Heater is amazing but we got a oil heater to keep the room warm which keep the place very nice and the heater clicks on less. Save propane. When super cold and it keeps clicking on so the little heater is a lifesaver. With out it propane is out very fast. If you can't do 2 ac budget or one is enough she can nap in your room my son hangs out in ours or the living room if he is warm in his by afternoon his room is cooling off and he goes in his. I think that is all the things we find to help :).

that is some great info.  We have been researching like crazy. Jayco seems to be what my wife likes and myself also. We were planning on getting a tiny house from a website but I told her to consider an RV. I need to research more info on the heating and Ac things this would be our first ever rv. We will be moving it around with a Ford F-350. So I'm not@too@worried about that. But defiantly some great input and information from you that i will pass onto my wife.  Thank you so much.

yeah your truck will tow the trailer no problem. My husband wanted to get a new Ford F-350 let's say it came down to having a truck but no house or house and wait for a sale on the truck. Since his credit is not amazing it's acceptable so he couldn't  swing both. So we are still working on something to tow us if we feel like going on vacation. Right now we are not going anywhere anytime soon. For the ac and heat have questions please feel free to ask and I can ask him why we went with the options we went with and how much our heater voltage is and things he looked alot into it as well. Also it was 4 months and two weeks I forgot. till the trailer came in I forgot. It was a saga for the trailer to come in. Lucky us it was during the summer while we were enrolling our son for school so his life wasn't to disrupted and his school wasn't effected. The trailer has more openness then a tiny home and easy to pack up and move. I got nothing against a tiny home it just wasn't a good option for our family and I like the trailer way way more :). This things has many nooks for storage but helps when you downsize so you can figure what goes where a shed is a great idea. We will get one has to be a specific size approved by the park we are at. Have questions I can ask my husband and be more then happy to help you out. We are a family of 3 and two small dogs and are very comfortable. The bed we have a "queen" in our room it's not a full normal queen it's a camping queen so it's a little smaller closer to a full size bed. Yeah if we would have known this we would have sacrifice walking space and gotten the king! His a large enough and we always hogs the middle or he stretches out and his elbow is by my face or head haha. If our son want to stay with us it gets even more snug lol. We are going to get a new mattress eventually the one that it comes with is rough....we have a bed foam topper has made a huge improvement since we weight more then my son. Who seems perfectly happy with his mattress as is till he tells us other wise we will get him support when he ask for it. So yeah he is finding sleep is more difficult for him till he is comfortable.

素材（生地）が兎に角すきで、世界中の生地を見せていただくんですが、いつも難しいと思うのは、どんなに素材が高級で良い素材であってもそれだけでは良い服にはならないというのが難しい。というのも、何かを作って変なものになるというのでは無くて、、、長く着れるのが良い服と私は思ってはいるけど、風合いが良い高級素材は耐久性に乏しかったりする。どんな服が良い服というのがブレないで継続して服を出していくのが、”ブランド”というものなのかなっと思います。建築を学ぶために大学に入ってすぐに建築士の教授に「どんな建築が良い建築なんですか？」という質問をした時に、「どんな建築が良い建築なのかを考え続けるのが建築家だ」という答えをもらって、それはとても難しいことのようにも思ったけど、それはとても楽だなっとも思いました。最高といわれる物に、負け続けて追いつこうとする学びよりも、だれかにとって最高を求める学びの方が意味が大きいと思えたから。このＰコートはドレステリアの定番としているものをベースに素材をしなやかで柔らかく保温性の高いものに変更して、型紙もそれに合わせて変更しました。 ..

Having a bit of   moment over here. I recently saw Kenneth Branagh’s new film Murder on the Orient Express. Having grown up with Masterpiece Mystery, and David Suchet as my beloved Poirot, I know the story line well. But it did not affect my enjoyment of the film. It’s a gorgeous production, with gorgeous costumes and yes, gorgeous actors 😀. The English penchant for crime novels is world renowned, and I’ve never met a murder mystery I didn’t like. Anyways, up on the blog ☝️I’ve posted some musings on moral relativism in response to Christie’s most intriguing caper. Even though many of us know the ending, the morality of the take is nuanced and may explain why it continues to intrigue us. Even Kenneth Branagh thought it needed another go.
